The paper deals with parsing structured knowledge graphs from textual descriptions, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a neural dependency parser, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The parser is trained end-to-end using neural networks, which is a machine learning (ML) technique, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the parser on image retrieval applications, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
